comments.body:
@lsm5 this is the way I'm leaning, and I'll just share it with the team internally.

We just have to be transparent with users.  Because it's building in the public, using possibly leaked-before-we-found-out credentials.  So the snap packages must not (EVER) be used for anything mission-critical or in any trusted environment.  They're for testing only, you keep both pieces if anything breaks.

OTOH, this is no different from the windows or darwin `podman-remote` binaries we publish from automation.
